Now, to solve this, the world's largest dewatering system has been created.

108
00:07:30,265 --> 00:07:32,920
沿THE LINE这段区域钻设了500口水井，
500 wells were drilled along this stretch of the line.

109
00:07:32,919 --> 00:07:35,448
每口井底都安装了一台水泵。
each equipped with a water pump at its bottom.

110
00:07:35,448 --> 00:07:39,024
系统以每小时90,000立方米的速度抽水，
Water is pumped out at a rate of 90,000 cubic meters an hour

111
00:07:39,024 --> 00:07:43,315
输送至沉淀池，在那里对水质进行检测。
or towards a settlement pond where the quality of the liquid is checked.

112
00:07:43,315 --> 00:07:49,199
之后，水经过过滤，通过一系列排放管道被抽送入海。
From there, the water is filtered and pumped out to sea in a series of discharge pipes.

113
00:07:49,199 --> 00:07:52,499
一期工程的基础施工已接近尾声，
Work on the foundations for phase 1 is nearly complete,

114
00:07:52,499 --> 00:07:57,119
